# `while` vs `for`

| `while`                                                   | `for`                                        |
| --------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Used when you don't know how many times the loop will run | Used when you know the number of repetitions |
| Needs a counter variable                                  | Counter handled automatically                |
| Easier to create infinite loops                           | Safer and cleaner                            |
| More flexible                                             | Simpler for counting                         |

